#{{chemistry}} any [[salt]] of [[chromic acid]]; in [[solution]] the [[yellow]] chromate [[anion]] (CrO<sub>4</sub><sup>2-</sup>) is in [[equilibrium]] with the [[orange]] [[dichromate]] anion (Cr<sub>2</sub>O<sub>7</sub><sup>2-</sup>), the [[relative]] amount of each [[ion]] [[depend]]ing on the [[pH]]; they are both very [[powerful]] [[oxidizing agent]]s

